01000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-111202727%2Cimgsize-621966.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fthankful-what-ex-union-minister-suryakanta-patil-said-after-resigning-from-bjp%2Farticleshow%2F111202755.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ex-Union%20minister%20Suryakanta%20Patil%20resigned%20from%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20on%20Saturday%2C%20dealing%20another%20blow%20to%20the%20party%20following%20unexpected%20results%20in%20the%20Maharashtra%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%20In%20her%20resignation%20letter%2C%20Patil%20explained%20her%20reasons%20for%20leaving%20the%20party.%20%26quot%3BI%20tried%20to%20seek%20personal%20appointment%20with%20state%20BJP%20chief%20Chandrashekhar%20Bawankule%2C%20but%20could%20not%20get%20an%20appointment%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20stated.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22There's%20A%2072%25%20Chance%20That%20An%20Asteroid%20May%20Hit%20Earth%20On%20This%20Exact%20Day%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EUS%20space%20agency%20NASA%2C%20in%20a%20hypothetical%20exercise%2C%20has%20found%20that%20a%20potentially%20hazardous%20asteroid%20has%20a%2072%25%20chance%20of%20hitting%20the%20Earth%20and%20we%20may%20not%20be%20adequately%20prepared%20to%20prevent%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fnews-release%2Fnasa-partners-conduct-fifth-asteroid-impact-exercise-release-summary%2F%5C%22%3Eofficial%20report%20by%20the%20space%20agency%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20NASA%20conducted%20the%20fifth%20biennial%20Planetary%20Defense%20Interagency%20Tabletop%20Exercise%20in%20April.%20On%20June%2020%2C%20NASA%20unveiled%20the%20summary%20of%20the%20exercise%2C%20held%20at%20the%20Johns%20Hopkins%20Applied%20Physics%20Laboratory%20(APL)%20in%20Laurel%2C%20Maryland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20tabletop%20exercise%2C%20apart%20from%20NASA%2C%20included%20nearly%20100%20representatives%20from%20various%20US%20government%20agencies%20and%20international%20collaborators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20there%20are%20no%20known%20significant%20asteroid%20threats%20in%20the%20foreseeable%20future%2C%20this%20was%20done%20to%20assess%20the%20Earth's%20ability%20to%20respond%20effectively%20to%20the%20threat%20of%20a%20potentially%20hazardous%20asteroid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENASA%20stated%20that%20the%20hypothetical%20exercise%20also%20provided%20valuable%20insights%20about%20the%20risks%2C%20response%20options%2C%20and%20opportunities%20for%20collaboration%20posed%20by%20varying%20scenarios.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20planetary%20defence%20officer%20emeritus%20at%20NASA%20Headquarters%20in%20Washington%2C%20Lindley%20Johnson%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20uncertainties%20in%20these%20initial%20conditions%20for%20the%20exercise%20allowed%20participants%20to%20consider%20a%20particularly%20challenging%20set%20of%20circumstances.%20A%20large%20asteroid%20impact%20is%20potentially%20the%20only%20natural%20disaster%20humanity%20has%20the%20technology%20to%20predict%20years%20in%20advance%20and%20take%20action%20to%20prevent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Tabletop%20exercise%20summary%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9CDuring%20the%20exercise%2C%20participants%20considered%20potential%20national%20and%20global%20responses%20to%20a%20hypothetical%20scenario%20in%20which%20a%20never-before-detected%20asteroid%20was%20identified%20that%20had%2C%20according%20to%20initial%20calculations%2C%20a%2072%25%20chance%20of%20hitting%20Earth%20in%20approximately%2014%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ETo%20be%20precise%2C%20%E2%80%9C72%25%20chance%20of%20Earth%20impact%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2Fttx5-quicklook-report-final.pdf%3Femrc%3D66748d3b531ab%5C%22%3E12%20July%202038%3C%2Fa%3E%20(14.25%20years%20warning%20time).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHowever%2C%20this%20preliminary%20observation%20is%20not%20sufficient%20to%20precisely%20determine%20the%20asteroid's%20size%2C%20composition%2C%20and%20long-term%20trajectory%2C%20added%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ETalking%20about%20the%20Earth's%20key%20gaps%2C%20the%20summary%20highlighted%2C%20%E2%80%9CDecision-making%20processes%20and%20risk%20tolerance%20not%20understood.%20Limited%20readiness%20to%20quickly%20implement%20needed%20space%20missions.%20Timely%20global%20coordination%20of%20messaging%20needs%20attention.%20Asteroid-impact%20disaster%20management%20plans%20are%20not%20defined.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIt%20is%20worth%20noting%20that%20this%20was%20the%20first%20exercise%20to%20use%20data%20from%20NASA's%20DART%20(Double%20Asteroid%20Redirection%20Test)%20mission.%20DART%20is%20the%20first%20in-space%20demonstration%20of%20a%20technology%20for%20defending%20the%20planet%20against%20potential%20asteroid%20impacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EDART%20has%20also%20confirmed%20that%20a%20kinetic%20impactor%20could%20change%20the%20trajectory%20of%20an%20asteroid%2C%20stated%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20report%20informed%20that%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20Earth%20will%20have%20time%20to%20evaluate%20and%20respond%20to%20a%20potentially%20hazardous%20asteroid%2C%20NASA%20is%20developing%20NEO%20Surveyor%20(Near-Earth%20Object%20Surveyor).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENEO%20Surveyor%20is%20an%20infrared%20space%20telescope.%20It%20is%20designed%20specifically%20to%20expedite%20humanity's%20ability%20to%20discover%20most%20of%20the%20potentially%20hazardous%20near-Earth%20objects%20many%20years%20before%20they%20could%20become%20an%20impact%20threat.%20NASA's%20NEO%20Surveyor%20will%20be%20launched%20in%20June%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719122760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F3jjudlqg_asteroid_625x300_13_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-exercise-finds-asteroid-with-72-chance-of-hitting-earth-5950284%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22US%20space%20agency%20NASA%2C%20in%20a%20hypothetical%20exercise%2C%20has%20found%20that%20a%20potentially%20hazardous%20asteroid%20has%20a%2072%25%20chance%20of%20hitting%20the%20Earth%20and%20we%20may%20not%20be%20adequately%20prepared%20to%20prevent%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-exercise-finds-asteroid-with-72-chance-of-hitting-earth-5950284%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-exercise-finds-asteroid-with-72-chance-of-hitting-earth-5950284%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-exercise-finds-asteroid-with-72-chance-of-hitting-earth-5950284%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mcap%20of%203%20of%20top-10%20most%20valued%20firms%20jumps%20Rs%201.06%20trn%2C%20HDFC%20Bank%20shine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719122710000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-11%2F06%2Fthumb%2Ffeaturecrop%2F400X400%2F1699294066-9942.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fmcap-of-3-of-top-10-most-valued-firms-jumps-rs-1-06-trn-hdfc-bank-shine-124062300135_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Last%20week%2C%20the%20BSE%20benchmark%20Sensex%20climbed%20217.13%20points%20or%200.28%20per%20cent%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fmcap-of-3-of-top-10