ump%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20how%20tough%20they%20are.%20He%20didn't%20like%20that%20idea%20too%20much%2C%20but%20actually%20not%20the%20worst%20idea%20I've%20ever%20had.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20won%20Pennsylvania%20in%202020%2C%20and%20his%20hopes%20of%20carrying%20the%20state%20in%20November's%20rematch%20with%20Trump%20will%20hinge%20in%20part%20on%20his%20ability%20to%20turn%20out%20Black%20voters%20and%20hold%20on%20to%20working-class%20voters%20in%20the%20state.%20A%20Bloomberg%20News%2FMorning%20Consult%20poll%20in%20May%20found%20Trump%20leads%20Biden%2048%25%20to%2046%25%20in%20Pennsylvania.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20has%20become%20a%20focal%20point%20for%20his%20reelection%20bid.%20According%20to%20an%20internal%20memo%20from%20the%20Trump%20allied%20super-PAC%2C%20Make%20America%20Great%20Again%20Inc.%2C%20the%20group%20has%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20center%20its%20efforts%20and%20funding%20across%20Pennsylvania.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20broadly%2C%20Biden%20has%20also%20struggled%20to%20sell%20blue-collar%20workers%2C%20important%20in%20states%20including%20Michigan%2C%20on%20his%20economic%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20been%20ramping%20up%20his%20campaigning%20after%20becoming%20the%20first%20former%20president%20convicted%20of%20a%20felony%2C%20in%20his%20New%20York%20hush-money%20trial.%20He%20has%20also%20managed%20to%20use%20the%20conviction%20to%20boost%20his%20war%20chest%2C%20with%20the%20campaign%20raising%20%24141%20million%20in%20May%2C%20surpassing%20the%20%2485%20million%20Biden%20raised%20that%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20visit%20to%20Washington%20on%20Saturday%20is%20his%20second%20this%20month.%20Last%20week%2C%20he%20returned%20to%20Capitol%20Hill%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20the%20Jan.%206%2C%202021%2C%20attack%20on%20the%20US%20Capitol%20by%20supporters%20looking%20to%20block%20certification%20of%20the%202020%20election%2C%20meeting%20with%20House%20and%20Senate%20Republic