r%20home%20countries%20like%20India%20and%20China%20after%20graduating%20from%20US%20colleges.%20He%20sought%20to%20replicate%20the%20same%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20presidential%20elections%20due%20in%20November%20is%20expected%20to%20see%20a%20second%20edition%20of%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20versus%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20in%20which%20immigration%20and%20deportation%20of%20illegal%20immigrants%20are%20among%20the%20key%20issues%20for%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20had%20earlier%20this%20year%20branded%20illegal%20immigrants%20%26quot%3Banimals%2C%20not%20human%26quot%3B%20at%20an%20election%20campaign.%20He%2C%20however%2C%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20podcast%20that%20he%20always%20supported%20a%20merit-based%20legal%20immigration%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BAll-In%26quot%3B%20podcast%20that%20he%20plans%20to%20offer%20Green%20Cards%20automatically%20as%20part%20of%20a%20diploma%20to%20students%20who%20graduate%20from%20a%20US%20college%2C%20which%20will%20help%20them%20continue%20their%20stay%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20podcast%20was%20hosted%20by%20Chamath%20Palihapitiya%2C%20Jason%20Calacanis%2C%20David%20Sacks%2C%20and%20David%20Friedberg%20-%20all%20venture%20capitalists%2C%20three%20of%20whom%20are%20immigrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20in%20the%20podcast%2C%20Trump%20recalled%20%26quot%3Bstories%20where%20people%20graduated%20from%20a%20top%20college%20or%20from%20a%20college%2C%20and%20they%20desperately%20wanted%20to%20stay%20here%2C%20they%20had%20a%20plan%20for%20a%20company%2C%20a%20concept%2C%20and%20they%20can't%20-%20they%20go%20back%20to%20India%2C%20they%20go%20back%20to%20China%2C%20they%20do%20the%20same%20basic%20company%20in%20those%20places...and%20they%20become%20multi-billionaires%20employing%20thousands%20and%20thousands%20of%20people%2C%20and%20it%20could%20have%20been%20done%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Green%20Card%20is%20an%20identity%20document%20for%20permanent%20residency%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20president%20further%20lamented%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20lose%20people%20from%20Harvard%2C%20MIT%2C%20from%20the%20greatest%20schools%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20reiterated%20his%20first-term%20policy%20of%20foreign%20students%20getting%20a%20Green%20Card%20after%20receiving%20a%20higher%20education%20degree%20in%20the%20STEM%20(science%2C%20technology%2C%20engineering%2C%20and%20math)%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnybody%20graduates%20from%20a%20college%2C%20you%20go%20in%20there%20for%20two%20years%20or%20four%20years%2C%20if%20you%20graduate%20or%20you%20get%20a%20doctorate%20degree%20from%20a%20college%2C%20you%20should%20be%20able%20to%20stay%20in%20this%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20force%20the%20brilliant%20people%2C%20the%20people%20that%20graduate%20from%20college%2C%20the%20people%20that%20are%20number%20one%20in%20their%20class%20from%20the%20best%20colleges%2C%20you%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20recruit%20these%20people%20and%20keep%20the%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20president%20asserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20some%20graduates%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20class%20can't%20even%20make%20a%20deal%20with%20the%20company%20because%20they%20don't%20think%20they%20will%20be%20able%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20country%2C%20but%20that%20is%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20to%20end%20one%20day%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20recent%20remarks%20were%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20immigration%20policies%20of%20his%20administration%20when%20he%20was%20in%20power%2C%20which%20included%20restrictions%20on%20green%20cards%20and%20visas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20over%20a%20million%20foreign%20students%20studying%20in%20colleges%20there%2C%20as%20of%20the%202022-23%20academic%20year%2C%20and%20this%20figure%20can%20only%20be%20expected%20to%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A